'''Sewadar''' is a [[Punjabi]] word for a [[volunteer]] who offers his/her [[service]]s to a [[Gurdwara]] or to the [[Community]]. It a person who performs [[Sewa]] (Work, assistance of any kind) without looking for any physical reward or any payment of any kind. A Sewadar helps purely because of his/her dedication to [[Guru]]/[[God]]. 





